Bart Schaefer wrote:
> Make any sort of mistake in zle-line-init, and the editor goes into an
> infinite loop.
> 
> E.g. (be sure you can kill this shell from somewhere else):
> 
> zle-line-init() {
>   setopt localoptions nomatch
>   echo not[a]pattern(that)matches{anything}
> }
> zle -N zle-line-init

Easy fix.

